image.altText: Forensic investigators outside a home on Topaz Drive at Mango Hill, north of Brisbane.

props.synopsis: Garry Allan Giles was sentenced to 11 years in jail after pleading guilty to the manslaughter of his 75-year-old mother Gloria McMaster in Mango Hill in 2018.

title.children: Niece of man who killed mother with hammer tells court she fears of being his next target

image.altText: Red emergency signage and entrance of the Queensland Children's Hospital at South Brisbane.

props.synopsis: Queensland Health does not know how many sexual assault victims have experienced delays in receiving medical care at its hospitals, a new report has found.

title.children: Qld sexual assault patient waited nine hours for forensic medical examination, report finds

image.altText: Elderly Torres Strait island man in hospital on dialysis machine

props.synopsis: First Nations people in the Torres Strait and Cape York are dying of preventable diseases at more than twice the overall rate for Queensland, prompting calls to return to a healthcare model developed 30 years ago.

title.children: Region's leaders say a failing health system is why they're going to 'too many funerals'

image.altText: Walters

props.synopsis: A tearful Kevin Walters has urged fans to stick with the Brisbane Broncos after the club announced he would no longer be head coach.

title.children: Emotional Walters urges fans to stick with Broncos as club begins search for new coach

image.altText: Queensland Fire and Rescue Service

props.synopsis: A review into the QFD's complaint system released on Friday found "a concerning upward trend in customer and stakeholder complaints", with the monthly average almost doubling from 28 in 2021 to "a troubling" 50 in 2023.

title.children: Queensland Fire Department's 'command and control' structure 'shielded perpetrators', report finds

image.altText: A person in a green full-head helmet and full green and yellow body suit crouched on a skateboard going down hill

props.synopsis: Sydney-born Harry Clarke has claimed the world title in men's downhill skateboarding less than eight months after a near-death experience. He hopes his win will help get the sport included in the Olympics.

title.children: Australian-born world downhill skateboarding champion nervously vomits before every race

image.altText: A graphic shows a food delivery app surrounded by a ghost-like haze.

props.synopsis: Have you noticed new dining options popping up on food delivery apps, but can't find their local shopfront? Chances are the food comes from a dark kitchen, also known as ghost or cloud kitchens.

title.children: Multiple restaurants from one location: your food might be being made in a ghost kitchen

image.altText: A man next to a dock

props.synopsis: Don Mills says his landlord hiked his maintenance fees at Brisbane's Dockside Marina nearly three times across eight years for repairs that never got finished and the marina has been fenced off to the public for over a year.

title.children: Don's landlord kept hiking his maintenance fees for repairs that never got done

image.altText: Man speaks in front of microphones.

props.synopsis: Mayor Troy Thompson, who is being investigated by the crime and corruption watchdog for allegedly misrepresenting his military and education history, claims the premier's move is "political grandstanding".

title.children: Queensland premier seeks legal advice over future of embattled Townsville mayor

image.altText: A graphic illustrating a social network of the pro-chemical lobby

props.synopsis: This social network, hosting figureheads of the pro-chemical lobby, can't be tracked down in a Google search. It collates "wiki dossiers" of vocal opponents of pesticides and chemicals along with advice on how to influence public discourse. Among its members are high-profile Australian industry players.

title.children: High-profile Australian industry players part of invite-only social network where pro-chemical lobby shares 'wiki' dossiers of known critics

image.altText: A woman standing in front of some shrubs.

props.synopsis: At the level she works at in NSW, Erica Roberts says the equivalent pay in Queensland is an extra $4 an hour and she can make greater super contributions. Wage negotiations between the union and state government are ongoing.

title.children: Nurse who can see local hospital from her driveway commutes interstate to make more money

image.altText: Reece Walsh and Ezra Mam talk and laugh during a trainign session for Brisbane

props.synopsis: The NRL Integrity Unit is probing an alleged incident involving Brisbane Broncos players Reece Walsh and Ezra Mam in Bali.

title.children: NRL probes Brisbane Broncos's Reece Walsh and Ezra Mam over alleged Bali incident

image.altText: Treasurer Jim Chalmers talks National Accounts

props.synopsis: After days of speculation over who ordered public servants to take another look at the tax breaks, the treasurer has spoken up.

title.children: Jim Chalmers concedes he asked Treasury for negative gearing modelling

image.altText: optus 'yes' sign on glass fronted office block

props.synopsis: Optus failed to provide honest and credible communication during last year's phone outage, and should be forced to provide fair compensation in the event of another, a Senate committee has found.

title.children: Senate inquiry finds Optus failed to honestly communicate in 'potentially dangerous' mass outage

image.altText: Jim Chalmers and NDRC Chairman Zheng Shanjie sit at a wide desk in a formal meeting room.

props.synopsis: Jim Chalmers meets with his Chinese counterpart to discuss the country's flagging economy and how that may impact Australia, as well as some lingering trade bans and the test-firing of an intercontinental ballistic missile.

title.children: He's the first Australian treasurer to visit Beijing in 7 years. So what did the Chalmers' trip achieve?

image.altText: a julia creek dunnart snarling being held in someone's hand

props.synopsis: When researchers aren't in the field, they roll "hundreds and hundreds" of bait balls with the secret ingredient of bacon to lure the endangered marsupial into traps.

title.children: Peanut butter bacon balls could be the best hope for these tiny endangered marsupials

image.altText: Aerial shot of a group of houses, all of which have solar panels on their roof

props.synopsis: For decades, a big risk to Australia's electricity system has been excessive demand in summer. Now, it is excessive supply in spring.

title.children: Market operator issues first-ever low-demand warning as solar 'juggernaut' risks grid overload

image.altText: A satelitte image shows cranes at shipyard in Wuhan Shi, China

props.synopsis: One of China's nuclear-powered submarines sank earlier this year, a potential embarrassment for Beijing as it seeks to expand its military capabilities.

title.children: Senior US defence official claims Chinese nuclear-powered attack submarine sank earlier this year

image.altText: A pink funeral booklet that has CHARLOTTE O'BRIEN in the title

props.synopsis: Charlotte O'Brien was 12 years old when she took her own life earlier this month. Her parents want her story to be shared.

title.children: Parents honour 'beautiful and kind' daughter who took her own life after alleged bullying

image.altText: The exterior of a multi-storey building that reads "Novotel" behind a six-lane traffic light intersection.

props.synopsis: A man breaks through the ceiling of a Canberra hotel lobby after allegedly hiding in the building's roof cavity in an attempt to escape arrest for stealing a bag containing several car keys.

title.children: Man hides in ceiling cavity before break through into Canberra hotel lobby in a bid to escape arrest

image.altText: Darcy Fort training with the Brisbane Lions in Brisbane.

props.synopsis: The Brisbane Lions name Darcy Fort in place of injured ruck Oscar McInerney for Saturday's grand final, while Taylor Adams fails in his bid to make the Swans' extended squad.

title.children: Lions confirm ruck replacement for grand final as Swans make call on Adams

image.altText: A serious-looking older man in a dark suit stands behind a lectern in front of an Israeli flag.

props.synopsis: Israeli PM Benjamin Netanyahu says reports of an imminent ceasefire are incorrect, saying he "did not even respond" to the ceasefire proposal and has instructed the IDF to keep fighting with full force.

title.children: Netanyahu rejects call from US, Australia for immediate 21-day ceasefire in Lebanon

image.altText: A man with long blonde air wearing a navy singlet sitting on a chair

props.synopsis: As the inquest into Josh Warneke's death comes to an end, Ingrid Bishop says she is unable to grieve for her beloved son due to a lack of answers.

title.children: Mother of Josh Warneke says family has been let down by 'abysmal' system failures

image.altText: A big pig standing in front of feed buckets bearing the logos of the Brisbane and Sydney AFL teams while wearing their scarves

props.synopsis: In January, a Gippsland farmer set his pig Clement the challenge of picking this year's AFL grand final winner on live radio and, on Saturday, we will find out whether the big pig tip is on the money.

title.children: This year's AFL grand final winner was decided in January, if Clement the 'psychic' pig is correct

image.altText: A man watching football having an angry reaction

props.synopsis: The AFL and NRL grand finals are a time of celebration for many, but experts warn it can be a period of heightened risk for domestic violence. Berry Street, a domestic violence support service, is preparing for a busy weekend, after experiencing a 30 to 40 per cent increase in demand during the 2023 grand final weekend.

title.children: Footy, fans and family violence: Why experts say major sporting events are the 'perfect storm'

image.altText: A soldier covers his ears as a tank explodes

props.synopsis: Israel has been giving strong signals it plans to launch a ground invasion of Lebanon as part of its war against Hezbollah, but whether it has learnt from its last military campaign in the country remains to be seen.

title.children: What Israel can learn from its 2006 ground invasion of Lebanon, which 'failed completely'

image.altText: Anthony Albanese speaks in the Prime Minister's Courtyard.

props.synopsis: For many of us, COVID has become just a bad memory, despite its lasting and mixed legacies. But experts are urging that we learn from our mistakes and plan ahead.

title.children: Pandemics don't give much notice of their arrival — so Albanese is being urged to get ready

image.altText: A spotted fish with a fan-like dorsal fin, flappy pectoral fins and six crab-like legs over sand in a fish tank.

props.synopsis: Imagine wading in the shallows at the beach and tasting mussels and clams hidden under the sand — with your feet. A new study shows fish species evolved to do just that.

title.children: Sea robins have 'the body of a fish, wings of a bird, legs of a crab'. They can also taste with their 'feet'

image.altText: Two men in muscular outfits

props.synopsis: Two non-Victorian clubs are set to meet in the 2024 AFL Grand Final, prompting thousands of fans to travel interstate in the hopes of seeing their team win the premiership.

title.children: Fans flock to Melbourne's AFL grand final parade ahead of Swans and Lions blockbuster

image.altText: LOST PARADISE

props.synopsis: The US ticket-selling platform Lyte has shut down, leaving two Australian music festivals in the lurch.

title.children: 'We are taking this situation seriously': Aussie festivals respond after US ticketing agent shuts down

image.altText: Woman grocery shopping in dairy aisle

props.synopsis: A new report from the Australian Competition and Consumer Commission has found many Australians have lost trust in supermarkets as it investigates the mega grocers' market power and potential barriers to entry in the sector.

title.children: ACCC supermarket inquiry investigating Coles and Woolworths' market power and barriers to entry

image.altText: Anthony Albanese wears high-vis and a hard hat.

props.synopsis: Anthony Albanese has said any negative gearing changes must not constrain housing supply, but has pointed to research which says housing would become more affordable.

title.children: PM cools on negative gearing over supply fears, but evidence tells a different story

image.altText: Head shot of ABC Editorial Director Alan Sunderland.

props.synopsis: A Walkley-winning journalist who spent 40 years working for SBS and the ABC will head an independent review into the 2022 reports, including a story that included an "editing error in the audio" of helmet cam footage captured by commandos in Afghanistan.

title.children: ABC appoints Alan Sunderland to conduct independent review into Line of Fire reporting

image.altText: A bird's-eye view of a steel-frame dome structure on a concrete base, with cranes either side and a desert backdrop.

props.synopsis: High in the Chilean desert, the Extremely Large Telescope is taking shape. It promises sharper views of space than we've ever seen — but will Australian astronomers be able to use it?

title.children: 'We will not fail': The Extremely Large Telescope in Chile is astronomy's next big thing — if it works
